This paper presents a new data structure for fully-dynamic graph connectivity, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper focuses on the design and analysis of the data structure, and does not involve any experimental evaluation or application to a specific domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is the primary area for research on graph algorithms and data structures. The paper also involves some combinatorial and geometric arguments, which suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories. The paper's focus on worst-case and amortized time complexity suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.AL (Algorithms) as other possible sub-categories.
